---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";

const todaysDate: Date = new Date();
const birthday: Date = new Date(2000, 4, 16);
const age: number = Math.floor(
    (todaysDate.getTime() - birthday.getTime()) /
        (1000 * 60 * 60 * 24 * 365.25),
);

import profilePic from "../assets/profile_pic.jpg";
---

<section
    class="w-full p-4 mb-2 bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg dark:bg-gray-800"
>
    <div class="flex flex-row flex-wrap justify-around items-center">
        <article class="text-justify xl:flex-[70%]">
            <h2 class="mb-10 text-2xl font-bold">Who am I? (Boring version)</h2>
            <p class="mb-5">
                Immersed in the world of computer science from a very young age,
                I quickly became curious to understand the technologies that are
                part of our daily lives by tinkering and searching for
                information by myself.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-5">
                That's why I decided to join ISIMA, a French engineering school
                specialized in computer science after my CPGE at the Edouard
                Branly high school in Lyon in order to acquire more information
                and to gain experience to make it my job. These trainings taught
                me rigor with the help of scientific knowledge like mathematics,
                industrial sciences, physics and, of course, computer science.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-5">
                My engineering studies have allowed me to acquire skills in C,
                C++, C# (.NET), Java and SQL which completes my knowledge
                acquired as a self-taught person, such as Python, HTML, CSS as
                well as some PHP. Finally, I use GNU/Linux and Windows operating
                systems.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-5">
                I then had the opportunity to do a double cursus in the
                University of Oklahoma thanks to my motivation to succeed. I
                discovered a new way of learning and a new culture.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-5">
                Besides my passion for technology, I also enjoy mountain biking,
                skiing and billiards (Blackball/Snooker/9-ball). In my free
                time, I also like to watch movies and series... and cat pictures
                of course. By the way, I also started playing violin at the age
                of 4 and traveled a lot.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-5">
                Finally, I studied three languages in addition of French (my
                native language): English (C1), Spanish (B1) and Mandarin
                (notions).
            </p>
        </article>
